Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.07,0:00:09.98,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1876\N(What is now) Philadelphia, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.90,0:00:16.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Well... I'll just be going!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.79,0:00:29.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm soaking wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.67,0:00:35.68,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad I'm somewhere warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.14,0:00:41.14,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd better get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.31,0:00:47.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:20.03,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 9\NBell's Responses"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:23.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where'd he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:30.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now. Don't get so down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.08,0:02:31.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.42,0:02:34.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I had plans for a telephone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:38.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But that idiot Bell beat me to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.59,0:02:44.60,Main,,0,0,0,,But it's not as if every one\Nof your inventions has worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:47.43,Main,,0,0,0,,You've always bounced back from your failures
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.43,0:02:51.19,Main,,0,0,0,,to keep trying new inventions. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:54.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't the most important thing\Nto keep moving forward?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.07,0:03:03.82,Main,,0,0,0,,I know that. It's obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.54,0:03:07.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:11.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:13.88,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you wearing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:17.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.34,0:03:21.43,Main,,0,0,0,,We were at the beach, and I happened\Nto touch the book and get sent here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.43,0:03:22.89,Main,,0,0,0,,At the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:36.11,Main,,0,0,0,,This is my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:39.15,Main,,0,0,0,,This is Mr. Graham Bell, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.15,0:03:41.11,Main,,0,0,0,,A pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:44.37,Main,,0,0,0,,You look nice and cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:46.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that Japanese folk clothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:47.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:52.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure... That's what we'll call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.58,0:03:56.00,Main,,0,0,0,,You do seem to know a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:57.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I just love sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:00.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Understood. Wait one moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:02.88,Main,,0,0,0,,--Lately, chocolate has--\N--Mr. Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:06.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Excuse me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:12.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari traveled through time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.40,0:04:18.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah. What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:19.65,Main,,0,0,0,,And Rika--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.65,0:04:21.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, where's Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:24.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:28.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Big Sis disappeared into the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:31.62,Main,,0,0,0,,N-Not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:35.04,Main,,0,0,0,,What did she mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:37.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:40.05,Main,,0,0,0,,What, indeed, did she mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:44.13,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'll be back soon, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.13,0:04:45.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:48.51,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the book my husband\Ngave you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.51,0:04:49.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.81,0:04:52.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Please explain everything to me, Shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:55.14,Main,,0,0,0,,You're hiding something from me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.14,0:04:59.11,Main,,0,0,0,,This has something to do with\NHayase's research, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:00.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Akira!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.24,0:05:05.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:20.96,Main,,0,0,0,,So, Dr. Hayase, your daughter\Nis the one you were waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:22.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:25.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Papa, you were waiting for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.09,0:05:26.09,Main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.09,0:05:27.59,Main,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:29.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:31.97,Main,,0,0,0,,The people you're waiting for\Nwill appear too, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:33.89,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.39,0:05:39.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Who's Mr. Bell waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.73,0:05:42.19,Main,,0,0,0,,The judges.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.19,0:05:45.53,Main,,0,0,0,,He wants to demonstrate the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:47.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:56.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, what were you doing\Nwith the book at the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:58.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Was Shun with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:05:59.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:01.75,Main,,0,0,0,,We were all at Grandpa's villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.75,0:06:05.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Then one of Mama's customers\Nlet us on his cabin cruiser...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:07.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Cruiser?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.17,0:06:10.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He's apparently super rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:14.31,Main,,0,0,0,,His name's Mr. Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.31,0:06:16.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Mikage's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:17.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.60,0:06:21.73,Main,,0,0,0,,He really likes Mama, okay?\NAnd he's handsome, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:26.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, Papa! You neglect Mama too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:30.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't blame me if Mama leaves you while\Nyou're searching for that book's secrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.12,0:06:33.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:36.41,Main,,0,0,0,,--Don't "Huh?" me!\N--Right this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:39.96,Main,,0,0,0,,My, how shameless!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.33,0:06:44.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:49.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, we should really do something\Nabout that outfit, first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:51.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Never mind. I'm going home anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.68,0:06:55.22,Main,,0,0,0,,No, let me explain things in more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.22,0:06:56.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:04.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Is your daughter okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.61,0:07:08.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think she went off somewhere to pout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:12.91,Main,,0,0,0,,She's probably back home\Nwith her friends about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:14.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.45,0:07:17.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:18.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:39.68,Main,,0,0,0,,This is cute! Thanks, Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:41.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:48.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, how close are Mikage and your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.66,Main,,0,0,0,,You want to know, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:58.70,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd love to eat some ice cream!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:07:59.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:04.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Delicious! Right, Mr. Bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:05.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:08.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the treat, Dr. Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:11.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, no problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:13.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, about Mikage and your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.93,0:08:16.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.97,0:08:19.10,Main,,0,0,0,,You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:22.18,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems like he comes by\Nher shop a lot, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Her shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.06,0:08:25.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:29.23,Main,,0,0,0,,You're finally worried about Mama, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:30.48,Main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.48,0:08:33.45,Main,,0,0,0,,She'll be fine. I trust her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.45,0:08:34.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:37.07,Main,,0,0,0,,A lot has happened between us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:41.45,Main,,0,0,0,,but we've both supported each other\Nas we pursue the things we love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.45,0:08:43.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Because we love what we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:45.87,Main,,0,0,0,,we'll both keep rushing, full speed ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.87,0:08:48.71,Main,,0,0,0,,We both know that about each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.71,0:08:53.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, that's not convincing when\Nyou've left her alone for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:54.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.93,0:08:57.76,Main,,0,0,0,,But I went to see her just this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:09.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I returned the glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:11.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:12.69,Main,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:16.49,Main,,0,0,0,,--Hey, Papa. I think I--\N--It's so hot. I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:21.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's call the judging over for today,\Nand do the rest at another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.45,0:09:24.25,Main,,0,0,0,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:27.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, if it isn't Mr. Bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:28.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Dom Pedro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:32.67,Main,,0,0,0,,What a coincidence, meeting you here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.67,0:09:34.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for taking care of me in Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:37.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Likewise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, as long as you're here, why not watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:45.27,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the pivotal moment when\Nthe telephone is introduced to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:47.35,Main,,0,0,0,,The pivotal moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:52.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'll begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:54.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Please go to the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.82,0:10:01.95,Main,,0,0,0,,This can still only be\Nspoken into from one end,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.95,0:10:04.91,Main,,0,0,0,,so I will speak to the emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:07.87,Main,,0,0,0,,standing in the next room over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.87,0:10:11.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Dom Pedro, can you hear what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:15.17,Main,,0,0,0,,I hear him! I can hear him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.63,0:10:18.97,Main,,0,0,0,,To be or not to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:21.51,Main,,0,0,0,,"To be or not to be."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.51,0:10:23.35,Main,,0,0,0,,That is the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:25.72,Main,,0,0,0,,"That is the question."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:32.23,Main,,0,0,0,,He talked through the machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:36.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Just like Mr. Bell said!\NIt's truly wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:42.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy for Mr. Bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.49,0:10:45.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, it gave me goosebumps!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:49.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, by showing us all of these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:51.58,Main,,0,0,0,,I think there's something\Nthe book wants us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.58,0:10:53.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:57.96,Main,,0,0,0,,The history of the telephone\Nrelies on many strange coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:10:59.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Coincidences?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:11:03.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bell was a teacher\Nat a school for the deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:06.47,Main,,0,0,0,,To teach deaf people how to speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:08.68,Main,,0,0,0,,he wanted to portray sounds visually.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.68,0:11:12.52,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what got him started on his research.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:16.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Then on June 2nd, 1875,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:20.11,Main,,0,0,0,,something happened that inspired him to\Ndiscover the principle behind the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:22.61,Main,,0,0,0,,His assistant, Thomas Watson,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:25.95,Main,,0,0,0,,plucked a reed while trying to\Nremove it from an electromagnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.95,0:11:30.12,Main,,0,0,0,,accidentally sending the sound\Ntraveling through the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.12,0:11:33.08,Main,,0,0,0,,After that, he tried many\Ndifferent configurations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:36.63,Main,,0,0,0,,until March 10th, 1876.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.63,0:11:39.38,Main,,0,0,0,,This time, Bell accidentally\Nspilled acid on his pants
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.63,Main,,0,0,0,,and cried out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:45.80,Main,,0,0,0,,That was the first time a person's\Nvoice was transmitted via telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.80,0:11:50.68,Main,,0,0,0,,And today, June 25th, 1876,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:56.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Dom Pedro, the emperor of Brazil, and\NMr. Bell happened to reunite at the exhibition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:12:01.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Previously, the emperor had come\Nto observe his schools for the deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:03.07,Main,,0,0,0,,What a lot of coincidences!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:06.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bell must have been a lucky person!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:08.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I think there's more to it than luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:09.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.66,Main,,0,0,0,,"When it comes to destiny,\Nthere are no coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.66,0:12:17.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Before a man meets his destiny,\Nhe builds it for himself."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:19.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you ever heard those words?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:21.92,Main,,0,0,0,,No. What do they mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.92,0:12:25.80,Main,,0,0,0,,The father of Mr. Bell's fiancée told him
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:28.97,Main,,0,0,0,,that he should focus on\Nthe invention of the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:33.02,Main,,0,0,0,,But because he wouldn't give up\Non the school or the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:37.98,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe that's the reason\Nhe got this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:41.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Because he wouldn't give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.53,0:12:44.57,Main,,0,0,0,,When you find something you love,\Nyou don't want to give up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:47.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.37,0:12:50.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Finding something you love is amazing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:54.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you found something like that yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.08,0:12:57.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Me? I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.54,0:13:01.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Rei, to make you take Rika.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:03.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.38,0:13:05.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Rika, dear, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:06.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:14.85,Main,,0,0,0,,We'll talk about the details inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:15.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:40.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.96,0:13:41.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:43.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... Akira?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:50.72,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mari. She found us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:54.39,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not your fault, Waka. It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:13:55.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:13:58.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, I don't want to hear that from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:02.52,Main,,0,0,0,,S-So, Akira...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:03.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.69,0:14:04.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:09.36,Main,,0,0,0,,It has been some time.\NYou seem as well as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.36,0:14:12.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Even though I saw you just last morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:16.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Last morning? When?\NYou clearly don't know how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:17.83,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:20.75,Main,,0,0,0,,But we swore our eternal devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.75,0:14:24.00,Main,,0,0,0,,on that beach before the setting sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:28.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Create what we imagine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:31.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. So I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.01,0:14:34.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Really. You just believe whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.93,0:14:37.02,Main,,0,0,0,,But this is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:39.98,Main,,0,0,0,,I've never communicated like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.98,0:14:44.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, I'm starting to believe\Nthat our time traveling
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:47.74,Main,,0,0,0,,will some day connect us to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.74,0:14:49.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:52.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Seeing Mr. Bell here confirmed it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:54.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Investigate things you're curious about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:56.95,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the entryway to loving something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:14:59.62,Main,,0,0,0,,The entryway to loving something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.62,0:15:02.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I guess it's time to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.33,0:15:03.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:09.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:10.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.84,0:15:13.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye. I'm happy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:16.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, Akira, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:25.52,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought he was a curious person, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.52,0:15:27.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Your father went home, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.94,0:15:29.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:34.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I wanted to thank him, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.37,0:15:38.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Dr. Hayase,\NI was able to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:40.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:45.29,Main,,0,0,0,,My work with the telephone was a success,\Nand I didn't have to quit my school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:48.76,Main,,0,0,0,,It was because of him\Nthat I could pursue both.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:50.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:54.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Please convey to him my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:56.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:16:00.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, watching you and Papa
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:03.56,Main,,0,0,0,,made me feel like I want\Nto work really hard, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:07.98,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to find something I love!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:09.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:12.70,Main,,0,0,0,,There are many interesting\Nthings in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:15.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:16.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.12,0:16:24.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? It won't turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.58,0:16:27.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.75,0:16:29.30,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:31.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:35.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari... Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:38.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Strange. This has never happened before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:41.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:43.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun? Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:44.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.31,0:16:45.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:48.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, don't force it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:52.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Shun? Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:58.03,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:02.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:04.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:06.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, what's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:10.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari will be able to come back, won't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:12.09,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right! Isn't it, Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.92,0:17:17.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:20.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll go to get her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:21.81,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:25.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I know where Mari is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:27.06,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll travel with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:29.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me go instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:30.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:34.94,Main,,0,0,0,,If I give her that, then at least\NMari can get back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.94,0:17:36.49,Main,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:38.07,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:41.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I know how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:43.24,Main,,0,0,0,,It'll work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:45.00,Main,,0,0,0,,No... I'll work it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:56.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, take care of Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:17:57.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:01.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, can you watch these coordinates\Non the TSS and support me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.30,0:18:02.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:04.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.73,0:18:10.11,Main,,0,0,0,,If Mari and I don't return,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:12.82,Main,,0,0,0,,it will change the future\Nwritten in this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.82,0:18:15.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't think that will be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:19.32,Main,,0,0,0,,What do I do? What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:21.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, please, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.87,0:18:25.70,Main,,0,0,0,,No, no, no! I can't calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.08,0:18:30.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:32.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:34.21,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for the disturbance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:35.30,Main,,0,0,0,,N-Not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:37.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, give me your compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:38.84,Main,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:47.14,Main,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.14,0:18:48.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:53.23,Main,,0,0,0,,It looks like water and sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.57,0:18:57.78,Main,,0,0,0,,When I fell into the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.61,0:18:59.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.16,Main,,0,0,0,,I've managed to fix the error.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:05.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness! That's the Shun I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.70,0:19:08.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Now we can go back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:10.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Assuming we can reactivate\Nthe armillary compass
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:13.63,Main,,0,0,0,,and link it to the TSS, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.64,0:19:26.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, can you confirm the AM2 coordinates?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:33.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It's there! It's on the screen, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:35.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.19,0:19:39.61,Main,,0,0,0,,The world truly is full of mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:42.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:45.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.37,0:19:46.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Neither will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:19:50.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:51.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:53.63,Main,,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.83,0:19:57.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Hold on. So we can go back together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:19:58.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:00.13,Main,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:06.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:13.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:15.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.15,0:20:16.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:18.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.98,0:20:20.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:21.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:24.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you know how worried we all were?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:27.24,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.24,0:20:29.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Never do this again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.24,0:20:30.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:35.71,Main,,0,0,0,,It's true that you've both leaped\Ninto the past without fear before,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.71,0:20:39.30,Main,,0,0,0,,but there's a chance something like this\Ncould happen again in the future, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:41.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.13,0:20:44.55,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right! So make me a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:47.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Never use this system again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:51.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Then give me the key to the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:20:56.56,Main,,0,0,0,,And those, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:05.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:07.91,Main,,0,0,0,,And with that resolved, I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:09.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:14.46,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.46,0:21:18.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess I should have told you\Nabout Papa sooner, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:21.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But I didn't want to worry you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.26,0:21:25.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.88,0:21:28.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, everyone come by my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.14,0:21:30.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Rei and Rika are waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.39,0:21:32.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll make something delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.27,0:21:33.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:34.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:42.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, that dress is really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.69,0:21:47.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I left my bathing suit in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:03.25,Main,,0,0,0,,According to the report,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:07.88,Main,,0,0,0,,that day, there was no trace of\NMari Hayase entering the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:09.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Which means
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.14,0:22:14.02,Main,,0,0,0,,she could have transported from\Nthe beach to the laboratory?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.02,0:22:15.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.06,0:22:18.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems almost certain that he completed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.81,0:22:20.77,Main,,0,0,0,,the matter transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.77,0:22:21.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:25.19,Main,,0,0,0,,We can't turn back from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:26.94,Main,,0,0,0,,The die has been cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.94,0:22:27.70,Main,,0,0,0,,The die has been cast.\N"Next Episode: Hertz's Pride"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.70,0:22:29.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Hertz's Pride"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:00.66,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:02.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.96,0:24:04.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.33,0:24:07.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Bell's telephone converted\Nsound into electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.71,0:24:12.01,Main,,0,0,0,,but he also tried experiments\Nto turn sound into light!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.01,0:24:13.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Into light?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.30,0:24:18.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Reflect a laser light off aluminum\Nfoil attached to a paper cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.22,0:24:23.73,Main,,0,0,0,,and when that light touches a photocell\Nattached to a deck and a speaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:26.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.65,0:24:29.03,Main,,0,0,0,,I heard a voice come from the speaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:32.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.20,0:24:35.66,Main,,0,0,0,,The reflected light is trembling?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.66,0:24:40.45,Main,,0,0,0,,The vocal oscillations are converted into\Nlight oscillations and send the sound along.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.45,0:24:44.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Sending messages with light\Nwould be really handy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.54,0:24:47.96,Main,,0,0,0,,But in this system, the light\Ndisperses and weakens,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.96,0:24:50.21,Main,,0,0,0,,so you can't achieve\Nlong-distance communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.21,0:24:51.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.55,0:24:56.43,Main,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, there's\Na thing called a heliograph...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.43,0:24:58.01,Main,,0,0,0,,I know that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.01,0:25:00.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It's the kind that's light flashes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.52,0:25:01.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.39,0:25:05.35,Main,,0,0,0,,You use the lengths of the light\Nflashes to send messages in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.35,0:25:08.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Just like Mr. Morse's code!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.48,0:25:12.44,Main,,0,0,0,,But this can't travel too far either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.44,0:25:13.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.28,0:25:17.82,Main,,0,0,0,,For a long time, it was impossible to achieve\Nlong-distance light-based communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.82,0:25:17.91,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\N\NBut thanks to the invention of optical fiber,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.91,0:25:21.04,Main,,0,0,0,,"Light" "Optical fiber"\N"Light bounces back and forth as it travels"\N\NBut thanks to the invention of optical fiber,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.04,0:25:25.37,Main,,0,0,0,,"Light" "Optical fiber"\N"Light bounces back and forth as it travels"\Nwe can now send fast,\Nlong-distance communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.37,0:25:25.41,Main,,0,0,0,,we can now send fast,\Nlong-distance communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.41,0:25:29.75,Main,,0,0,0,,So eventually, the world was linked by light!
